Comment: Start of JSON for AQUATOX Volume model

Locale.Locale_Comment: Site data record is required; not all parameters are utilized by every model.  Parameter definitions and units in Site_Record_Specs.docx

SV.Comment: The type indicator above must be included to indicate this is an AQUATOX Volume TStateVariable.
SV.Comment_InitialCond: Initial condition water volume in units of cubic meters

output.Comment: AQUATOXTSOutput is where integratedmodel outputs for this state variable are stored.

Loadings.Comment_Loadings: Known-Value site volume data in cubic meters, constant or time series.

Alt_Loadings.Comment_Alt_Loadings0: Inflow of water in cubic meters per day constant or time series goes here.

Alt_Loadings.Comment_Alt_Loadings1: Discharge of water in cubic meters per day constant or time series goes here.

Alt_Loadings.Comment_Alt_Loadings2: This loading is not used for TVolume

PSetup.PSetup_Comment: Setup data record is required to define how integration will take place; not all parameters are utilized by every model.  Parameter definitions and units in Setup_Record_Specs.docx
